Note:
Runa Standard Library: File I/O Utilities

Provides comprehensive file input/output operations for Runa programs.

Idiomatic Runa code uses natural language operators:
  Let content be read file "data.txt"
  Write content to file "output.txt"
  Let files be list files in directory "docs"
  Let size be size of file "large.dat"

For advanced/AI-generated code, use helpers:
  Let result be read with path as filename
  Let result be write with path as filename and data as content
  Let result be copy with source as src_path and destination as dst_path
:End Note

Process called "read" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return read file path

Process called "write" that takes path as String and data as String returns None:
    Write data to file path
    Return None

Process called "append" that takes path as String and data as String returns None:
    Append data to file path
    Return None

Process called "exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Return file path exists

Process called "size" that takes path as String returns Integer:
    Return size of file path

Process called "copy" that takes source as String and destination as String returns None:
    Copy file from source to destination
    Return None

Process called "move" that takes source as String and destination as String returns None:
    Move file from source to destination
    Return None

Process called "delete" that takes path as String returns None:
    Delete file at path
    Return None

Process called "read_binary" that takes path as String returns List[Integer]:
    Return read binary file path

Process called "write_binary" that takes path as String and data as List[Integer] returns None:
    Write binary data to file path
    Return None

Process called "read_lines" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Return read lines from file path

Process called "write_lines" that takes path as String and lines as List[String] returns None:
    Write lines to file path
    Return None

Process called "is_file" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Return is file at path

Process called "is_directory" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Return is directory at path

Process called "is_symlink" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Return is symbolic link at path

Process called "get_modified_time" that takes path as String returns Number:
    Return last modified time of file path

Process called "get_created_time" that takes path as String returns Number:
    Return creation time of file path

Process called "get_access_time" that takes path as String returns Number:
    Return last access time of file path

Process called "get_permissions" that takes path as String returns Integer:
    Return file permissions of path

Process called "set_permissions" that takes path as String and mode as Integer returns None:
    Set file permissions of path to mode
    Return None

Process called "get_owner" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return owner of file path

Process called "get_group" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return group of file path

Process called "create_directory" that takes path as String returns None:
    Create directory at path
    Return None

Process called "create_directories" that takes path as String returns None:
    Create directories recursively at path
    Return None

Process called "list_directory" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Return list of files in directory path

Process called "list_directories" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Return list of subdirectories in directory path

Process called "walk_directory" that takes path as String returns List[List[String]]:
    Return recursive directory listing of path

Process called "get_absolute_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return absolute path of path

Process called "get_relative_path" that takes path as String and base as String returns String:
    Return relative path from base to path

Process called "join_paths" that takes paths as List[String] returns String:
    Return joined path from paths

Process called "split_path" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Return split path components

Process called "get_extension" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return file extension of path

Process called "get_filename" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return filename of path

Process called "get_directory" that takes path as String returns String:
    Return directory of path

Process called "change_directory" that takes path as String returns None:
    Change current working directory to path
    Return None

Process called "get_current_directory" returns String:
    Return current working directory

Process called "get_temp_directory" returns String:
    Return system temporary directory

Process called "get_home_directory" returns String:
    Return user home directory

Process called "create_temp_file" that takes prefix as String and suffix as String returns String:
    Return path of created temporary file with prefix and suffix

Process called "create_temp_directory" that takes prefix as String returns String:
    Return path of created temporary directory with prefix

Process called "lock_file" that takes path as String returns None:
    Acquire exclusive lock on file path
    Return None

Process called "unlock_file" that takes path as String returns None:
    Release lock on file path
    Return None

Process called "truncate_file" that takes path as String and size as Integer returns None:
    Truncate file path to size bytes
    Return None

Process called "touch_file" that takes path as String returns None:
    Update access and modification times of file path
    Return None

Process called "compare_files" that takes file1 as String and file2 as String returns Boolean:
    Return true if file1 and file2 have identical content

Process called "get_file_hash" that takes path as String and algorithm as String returns String:
    Return hash of file path using algorithm

Process called "compress_file" that takes source as String and destination as String returns None:
    Compress file from source to destination
    Return None

Process called "decompress_file" that takes source as String and destination as String returns None:
    Decompress file from source to destination
    Return None 